      • getRoomOccupancy

        public double getRoomOccupancy(String room,
                      int minuteOfTheDay,
                      String user)
        Description copied from interface: RoomOccupancy
        Gets the probability (between 0 and 1) that the given user will be in the given room at the given moment of the day.
        Specified by:
        getRoomOccupancy in interface RoomOccupancy
        Parameters:
        room - the room name where the occupancy value is required.
        minuteOfTheDay - a specific time in the day in minute (between 0 (=00:00) and 1439 (=23:59)).
        user - the given user.
        Returns:
        the room occupancy is a value between 0 and 1 where 0 indicates that there the room is always empty and 1 indicates that the room is always occupied at the given moment of the day.
